message.content:
cs.NI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.OH

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper describes the development of a system that uses multiple node devices connected through the internet to transmit data to a database via web API.
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also likely as the paper describes the use of NodeMCU Arduino wrapper library, Google maps and firebase API along with JavaScript webapp to develop the system.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of the system for research on sound pollution in targeted areas, which has implications for society.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper describes the development of a webapp for real-time data visualization, which involves user interaction.
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a catch-all category that could apply if the paper does not fit neatly into any of the other categories.
